# Image assets

Organize all static images by category. Use WebP/AVIF sources; Next.js Image handles optimization.

```
public/images/
├── brand/
│   ├── logo.svg
│   ├── logo.png
│   └── favicon.ico
├── og/
│   ├── default.jpg          # 1200×630 — fallback OG image
│   ├── services/            # Per-service OG images
│   └── locations/           # Per-location OG images
├── heroes/
│   └── home-hero.webp
├── services/
│   └── {slug}.webp          # Service card thumbnails
├── projects/
│   └── {slug}.webp          # Project gallery
├── locations/
│   └── {slug}.webp          # Location page headers
└── placeholders/
    └── blur.webp              # Optional LQIP base64 source
```

## Rules

- **Naming:** kebab-case, match content slug (`handyman.webp`, `sherwood-park.webp`)
- **Hero images:** max 1920px wide, 16:9 or 4:3
- **OG images:** exactly 1200×630px
- **Alt text:** always set in data layer, never empty
- **Priority:** `priority={true}` only for above-fold LCP image (hero)
- **Remote images:** add hostname to `next.config.ts` `remotePatterns`
